using io = std::io
using math // Same as ``using namespace std`` in c++
/*
Also in Luna when someone does "import io{print}" then also they have to use io::print. The {print} signifies that u can't do io::other_func() . 
Use "using io" so that "print" works. Also due to {print}, only print function is imported even when u do using io
We dont have something like import http::* because u can just do import http and then do using http. Sure more clumky but it is a bad practice anyways
*/

// Important:- For when clause, unlike C++ switch case, you dont have to break at the end of each case because there is no fallthrough. Each case is independent and only one case will be executed. 
// So no need for break to prevent fallthrough.
//NOTE TO SELF:Do not add the feature to use continue for fall back. No. If continue is used then the loop in which the when clause is will continue and 
// not the when clause fallbacking
/*
For for loop of form 
loop var:iter{...}
The var is immutable by default but if u want to make it mutable then do 
loop mut var:iter{...}
